tweet: Amend. 3, if approved, would specify the members of the Univ. of Ala. Board of Trustees will be appointed from the U.S. congressional districts as they stood Jan. 1, 2018. It allows members to serve after age 70 & removes the state supt. of education as a required member.

tweet: Amend. 2, if approved by a majority of yes votes, would change the state constitution to say the broad public policy of the state is to support the rights of the unborn & specify the constitution does not protect an individual’s right to abortion or require funding of abortion.
